Reuniting people who shared a unique experience. People return to the army base they were moved to for safety as children in the early days of the Troubles.

[img]http://extraimago.com/images/2015/09/30/ae0e7422491a598df45cdfd083b26169.jpg[/img]

Reuniting people who have shared a unique experience in Northern Ireland's past.

Former child refugees, moved to the Republic of Ireland and safety during the early days of the troubles, return to the army base where they were sheltered. Also, nearly 20 years on, the plucky film festival organisers who managed to persuade Stephen Fry to come to west Belfast get to hear his take on the trip
